node.text:
📌 What is Amersfoort famous for? Amersfoort is famous for its historic and attractive city centre, with landmarks such as the famous Koppelpoort and the 15th century Onze Lieve Vrouwetoren (Our Lady tower). Its historical well preserved city centre offers a great shopping experiences catering for everyone.
🌎 Amersfoort, Netherlands 🇳🇱 
📸 @mvd_slt
🐾 Follow @best.city.shots

node.text:
📌 Kyoto, once the capital of Japan, is a city on the island of Honshu. It's famous for its numerous classical Buddhist temples, as well as gardens, imperial palaces, Shinto shrines and traditional wooden houses. It’s also known for formal traditions such as kaiseki dining, consisting of multiple courses of precise dishes, and geisha, female entertainers often found in the Gion district.
🌎 Kyoto, Japan 🇯🇵 
📸 @tomokotoamu
🐾 Follow @best.city.shots

node.text:
From Emilia, with love ❤️ 8 wonders to discover in Emilia Romagna

1. @FidenzaVillage, a shopping destination in the center of wonders where you can taste the flavors of Emilia and shop in more than 120 fashion brands (from A for Armani to Z for Zegna)
2. @castelloditabianoevents one of the most romantic castles in Italy with almost 1000 years of history
3. @montedellevigne, a romantic and folk vineyard where you can live a suggestive experience
4. @labirintodifrancomariaricci is the largest labyrinth in the world, a maze of bamboo over 3km long that houses a museum and a pyramid
5. @castell_arquato is one of the most beautiful Castles in Italy where the film Ladyhawke was shot
6. @anticacortepallavicina a mine of culatelli (the king of salami). Here you can discover the true secret of Emilian cuisine
7. @valtrebbiaofficial Bobbio an enchanted bridge in what according to Hemingway is "the most beautiful valley in the world"
8. The Rocca di Fontanellato, surrounded by an ancient moat, hides one of the most beautiful frescoed rooms in Italy

In a travel weekend you can combine nature, culture and fashion.
A journey that starts from Fidenza Village @thebicestervillagecollection
